cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the design and implementation of a probabilistic programming language, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The language is also designed for use in artificial intelligence applications (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of the language, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and the use of functional representations for probabilistic paradigms, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS).
